<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old boy was shot and critically wounded Thursday during a shooting in 
the Cadillac-Corning area of West Los Angeles that police said may have been 
gang-related. 
</P>
<P>
James Clements of Culver City was in extremely critical condition and on life 
support at Kaiser Foundation Hospital in Hollywood after being shot once in the 
head in the 2000 block of Corning Street shortly after midnight Wednesday, 
Detective Bill Humphry of the Los Angeles Police Department said. 
</P>
