<HEADLINE>
<P>
PATCHY GROUNDFOG SCORES WIN OVER ORAIBI IN FEATURE RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From the Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Patchy Groundfog overtook 9-5 favorite Oraibi deep in the stretch Thursday to 
win the $45,000 feature race at Hollywood Park by one length before a crowd of 
10,303. 
</P>
<P>
Patchy Groundfog, ridden by Corey Black, covered one mile on Hollywood Park's 
turf course in 1:34 1/5 and paid $6.80, $3.20 and $2.60. 
</P>
<P>
Oraibi, ridden by Laffit Pincay, crossed the finish line three-quarters of a 
length in front of Bon Vent and returned $3 and $2.40. 
</P>
<P>
Bon Vent, ridden by Gary Stevens, returned $3.20 to show. 
</P>
<P>
Oraibi led all the way until being caught and passed by Patchy Groundfog. 
</P>
</TEXT>
