<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MARCACHINI SCORES 31 IN NOTRE DAME WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM BROWN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
G. C. Marcachini scored 31 points, including two of Notre Dame High's three 
fourth-quarter field goals, as the Knights defeated Westlake, 56-51, Thursday 
night in the championship bracket of the Beverly Hills tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame will play Royal, a 69-62 winner over Culver City, Saturday for fifth 
place in the 16-team tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Knights advanced despite nearly blowing an eight-point lead heading into 
the fourth quarter. Employing frenzied full-court pressure, Westlake forced 
Notre Dame into 14 second-half turnovers, most during the initial moments of 
the fourth quarter when Westlake outscored the Knights, 7-0, to draw within 
42-41. 
</P>
<P>
However, Paul Hewitt and Marcachini combined for 11 points over the final four 
minutes to rescue the Knights (4-4). Marcachini also grabbed a game-high 12 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
John Van Spyk paced Westlake (4-4) with 12 points. The Warriors, who had 66 
turnovers in two games last week, were plagued again -- they had 21 miscues. 
</P>
<P>
In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Royal 69, Culver City 62 -- Four Highlanders scored in double figures and Royal 
outscored the Centaurs, 12-5, over the last two minutes in a 
championship-bracket game. 
</P>
<P>
Jared Byrne scored a team-high 12 points, Greg Laranjo and Chad Smith each 
scored 11 and Chris Moriarty added 10 as Royal improved to 5-2. 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa 65, St. Bernard 54 -- Eric Thomas scored 19 points and Eric Dyer added 
12 in the consolation quarterfinals as the Spartans (1-2) won for the first 
time in three games. 
</P>
<P>
Palisades 65, Crespi 59 -- Crespi fought back from a 41-27 halftime deficit in 
a consolation quarterfinal game but fell short. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi center Christian Fauria scored 15 of his 19 points in the second half to 
lead the surge. Rasaan Hall led the Celts with 23 points. TIM BROWN 
</P>
</TEXT>
