<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHILLIES ADD VATCHER TO BIG LEAGUE ROSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jim Vatcher, the leading hitter on the Cal State Northridge baseball team in 
1987, has been promoted to the Philadelphia Phillies' major league roster. 
</P>
<P>
Vatcher was named the Phillies' top minor-league prospect in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Last season he batted .301 with 30 doubles and 46 runs batted in at Class-A 
Clearwater of the Florida State League before moving on to double-A Reading 
(Pa.) in the Eastern League, where he batted .327 with 32 RBIs in 48 games. 
</P>
