<HEADLINE>
<P>
REASONS FOR GLUCOSE TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: An uncle of mine was referred for a glucose test because his doctor 
thought that he had diabetes. It turned out that his glucose level was not 
normal, but that he doesn't have diabetes. I thought that diabetes meant that 
you did not have a normal glucose level. What else could it be? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Diabetes is usually the cause of an abnormal blood glucose measurement. 
However, blood glucose also may be affected by severe stress, an overactive 
thyroid, pancreatic tumors and use of diuretics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
