<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sallinen Premiere Expected in L.A.: Peter Hemmings, general director of Los 
Angeles Music Center Opera, is expected to announce the world premiere today of 
Aulis Sallinen's fourth opera, "Kullervo," at the Music Center in early 1992. 
Hemmings will make the announcement in Helsinki, Finland, jointly with Ilkka 
Kuusisto, general manager of Finnish National Opera, which will produce the 
work at the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion, Feb. 22-March 1, 1992, in association 
with LAMCO. The Finnish contingent will furnish the leading singers -- led by 
baritone Jorma Hynninen, who is artistic director of the Finnish company -- the 
chorus and conductor Ulf Soderblom. The composer has fashioned his own libretto 
for "Kullervo," loosely basing it on the play "Kullervo" by the 19th-Century 
Finnish playwright Aleksis Kivi. SHAUNA SNOW 
