<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Petition for 'Homeroom': Parents and teachers in Watts have vowed to petition 
ABC to save "Homeroom," a canceled half-hour comedy series they say helps keep 
their kids in school. "All we're saying is give the show a chance," said Jim 
Goins, who counsels school dropouts in the Watts area. "There's not that many 
shows of color that deal with educational issues, and we're in a dilemma right 
now as far as having black male role models," Goins said. "Homeroom" stars 
Darryl Sivad as a man who gave up a lucrative job in advertising to teach at an 
inner-city school. SHAUNA SNOW 
