<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRST IMPRESSIONS: A SUSBSTANTIAL PORTION OF AMERICANA AT MARY'S LAMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUTH REICHL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cute. That's the word for the new, larger Mary's Lamb, which has moved up 
Ventura Boulevard to 10820 in Studio City. (The phone number is (818) 
505-6120.) It's wholesome, all-American look -- stenciled floor, walls covered 
with quilts and creamers that look like cows -- goes perfectly with its 
wholesome, all-American food. 
</P>
<P>
Even at lunchtime, there's jam on the table -- to slather on top of the 
biscuits that are sitting in the breadbasket. Lunch offerings include a large 
</P>
<P>
chopped salad filled with large chunks of chicken, avocado, bacon and cheese. 
There are good sandwiches (the cheese and grilled-onion topped meatloaf is 
memorable), various pastas and a fritata or two. Dinner offerings are along the 
same lines, but more substantial. If you like, you can also eat food from the 
take-out section (including fine fried chicken) while sitting at your table. 
And don't forget the all-American desserts: the banana-walnut cake is straight 
off the farm. RUTH REICHL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Mary's Lamb, at 10820 Ventura Blvd., has an all-American taste, 
including jam at lunch for biscuits. MINDY SCHAUER 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
