<P>
HOLOCAUST FUNDS THEFT: $16 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A leader of West Germany's Jewish community who died last year embezzled nearly 
$16 million in government funds intended for Holocaust survivors, according to 
a report released in West Berlin. The report added that attempts to get the 
money back have been unsuccessful. After the January, 1988, death of Werner 
Nachmann, the 62-year-old chairman of the Central Council of Jews in Germany, 
investigators found he had run a massive embezzlement scheme involving 
reparations paid by the West German government. 
