<TEXT>
<P>
The military rulers of Sudan are planning to revive Islamic sharia laws, 
Sudanese and diplomatic sources in Khartoum said. The Islamic laws are fiercely 
opposed by non-Muslim rebels fighting a civil war in the south, and their 
revival in the mainly Arab and Muslim north would diminish hopes of peace. The 
Sudan People's Liberation Army has been fighting a civil war since 1983 in the 
Christian and animist south. 
