<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BLACKBURN SCORES 18, BREA POUNDS KATELLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tammy Blackburn had 18 points to lead Brea-Olinda High School to a 70-43 
victory over Katella Thursday in a championship quarterfinal game of the 
Brea-Olinda girls' basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Aimee McDaniel had 17 points, Jinelle Williams had 13 and Jody Anton added 10 
for Brea (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
Karen Jensen had 16 for Katella (3-2). 
</P>
<P>
In other Brea-Olinda tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 64, South Torrance 41 -- Christine Garner had 23 points and 13 rebounds 
to lead Tustin (6-2) in its second-round game. 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 45, Fontana 44 (OT) -- Jenifer Harney had 18 points, including the 
winning basket with about a minute left in overtime for Esperanza (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
At the El Dorado tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 44, Whittier Christian 40 -- Cori Daldey had 15 points and Sheri Rhyne 
had 13 to lead Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
In the Santa Ana Valley tournament: 
</P>
<P>
University 42, Santa Ana Valley 34 -- Denise Gandara had 23 points and 20 
rebounds to lead University (5-2). 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague play: 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 41, Capistrano Valley 39 -- Guard Sig Lo had 14 points and Hollie 
Keeton 10 points and 19 rebounds to pace Valencia (1-3) at Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 47, Sonora 41 -- Briana Yoshina had 11 points and Theresa Korte had 
13 to lead El Dorado (4-1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
