<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fluorocarbon Earnings Dip: Fluorocarbon Co., the Laguna Niguel manufacturer, 
reported that while third-quarter sales were up 30%, earnings declined 13%. For 
the three months ended Nov. 4, net earnings totaled $2.2 million, compared to 
$2.5 million for the like quarter last year. Sales rose to $82.8 million from 
$63.5 million. Net income for the nine-month period declined 20%, to $6.5 
million from $8.1 million. Last year's figure included a one-time gain of $1 
million on sale of assets. Sales increased 37%, to $252.7 million from $184.3 
million. Peter Churm, chairman of the company, said the results reflected the 
acquisitions of Dixon, CHR and Bunnell, which were completed in February. 
Fluorocarbon manufactures polymer components for a wide range of industrial 
markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
