<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. MUSICIANS PLAN 3 HOLIDAY BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Tis the season to be charitable for musicians on the local pop music scene, 
who will lend their services to three holiday benefits this weekend. 
Concertgoers can do a good deed and catch performances in styles ranging from 
Jamaican reggae to blues, Cajun music, bluegrass and avant-garde rock. 
</P>
<P>
The sixth annual Noise for Toys benefit is a two-show affair, tonight and 
Saturday at the Doll Hut, 107 S. Adams St. (near the corner of Manchester 
Avenue) in Anaheim, with local rockers pooling their talent to collect toys and 
money for the Canyon Acres Home for Abused Children. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight's lineup: Dirk &amp; the Pugslies at 8 p.m., the Clints at 9, Rattlin' 
Bones at 10, the Fullerton All-Stars, with members of Cheezboy and Berlin, at 
11 p.m., and the Decadent Debutantes, the once-a-year group that gets together 
to play the Noise for Toys show, at midnight. On Saturday, Rhythm &amp; Booze 
plays at 8 p.m., Nevada Time at 9, Cheezboy at 10, Swingset at 11, the Decadent 
Debutantes at midnight, and the Joneses at 1 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Admission, only open to those 21 and older, is $5 or its equivalent in 
unwrapped new toys. Information: (714) 533-1286. 
</P>
<P>
The second annual Reggae Christmas Concert and Dance Benefit Show takes place 
Sunday from 5 to 11 p.m. at the Iglesia Community Center, 24671 Via Iglesia in 
Laguna Hills. The proceeds will go to the Orangewood Children's Home for abused 
and neglected children. 
</P>
<P>
StrangeJah Cole, the Jamaican ska veteran who now lives in Laguna Hills, will 
perform with singer Queen Rejoice and the Jah Cole Jammers, with backing by the 
714 Band. Sharing the bill is Jamaican reggae veteran Ras Michael and the Sons 
of Negus. The event also offers a chance to sample Jamaican style food, drinks 
and crafts. 
</P>
<P>
Admission is $7 for adults, $3 for children, with a discount for those who 
donate an unwrapped toy. Information: (714) 458-6471 or (714) 830-8381. 
</P>
<P>
The fifth annual Orange County Music for the Needy benefit features 15 acts 
playing from noon to midnight Sunday at the Coach House, 33157 Camino 
Capistrano, San Juan Capistrano. Christmas donations of money, canned goods, 
toys and other items will go to poor Orange County families designated by St. 
Barbara's Church in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
The lineup: D.O.M.E.S. at noon, the Sleepers at 12:45, Louisiana Cajun Trio at 
1:30, Dennis Roger Reed Band at 2:15, Eggplant at 3 p.m., James Harman Band at 
3:45, the Beat Pests at 4:30, National People's Gang at 5:15, Circadian Rhythm 
at 6 p.m., Wild Cards at 6:45, Wood &amp; Smoke at 7:30, Joe Wood Project at 
8:15, Don't Mean Maybe at 9 p.m., Big Drill Car at 9:45, Dick Dale at 10:30. 
</P>
<P>
Admission is $7 or its equivalent in canned foods or unwrapped new toys. 
Information: (714) 496-8930. 
</P>
</TEXT>
