</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOGOTA, Colombia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gonzalo Rodriguez Gacha, one of the most powerful drug traffickers in the 
world, was killed today during a shootout with police, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
According to police, Rodriguez Gacha, his 17-year-old son Freddy and 11 of his 
bodyguards were shot to death near the Colombian port of Covenas, on the 
Caribbean about 75 miles south of Cartagena. 
</P>
<P>
Gen. Carlos Casadiego, subdirector of the national police in Covenas, confirmed 
the death of Rodriguez Gacha, who is No. 2 in the notorious Medellin cartel, 
and the 12 others but had no further details. 
</P>
<P>
Pablo Escobar, the leader of the Medellin cartel, remains at large. 
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez Gacha and Escobar have been sought by U.S. and Colombian authorities 
since President Virgilio Barco Vargas ordered a crackdown on drug traffickers 
following the August slaying of a leading opposition presidential candidate. 
