<P>
SAM WHO TO HEAD FIELD OF 4 IN SPRINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A field of four headed by Sam Who was entered in Saturday's $100,000-added 
National Sprint Championship at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
Sam Who will be ridden by Laffit Pincay and was assigned 122 pounds for the 
ninth running of the six-furlong race for 3-year-olds and up. 
</P>
<P>
Others entered were Order, who will be ridden by Aaron Gryder and was assigned 
122 pounds; Olympic Prospect, who will be ridden by Alex Solis and was assigned 
120 pounds, and Ron Bon, who will be ridden by Gary Stevens and was assigned 
116 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Sam Who will make his first start since his fourth-place finish and subsequent 
disqualification for interference after the start in the Breeders' Cup on Nov. 
4. He set the track record this spring sprinting six furlongs in 1:08 flat May 
20. 
</P>
<P>
Olympic Prospect, known for his speed away from the gate, is expected to try to 
jump to a big lead in the short field and hold off any late challenges. The 
John Sadler trainee comes into the stake off an easy one and one-quarter length 
win in 1:08.2 Dec. 3, only two-fifths off Sam Who's record. 
</P>
<P>
If all four entries go to the post, the total purse will be $105,200 and the 
winner will collect $60,200. 
</P>
